OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F151A1776863482
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/6
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCPam Masters: a key figure in
OL,4,Cmodern British television presentation
OL,5,
OL,6,FAnd, of course, she helped ensure the
OL,7,Fchannel came together smoothly on air `
OL,8,Fdespite some initial problems with a
OL,9,Frevolutionary computerised transmission
OL,10,Fsystem.
OL,12,FShe took the view that because many of
OL,13,FC4's programmes were unfamiliar or
OL,14,Funconventional, Presentation should be
OL,15,Fmuch more straightforward.
OL,17,FYet C4 also established its own
OL,18,Fcharacter. I used to think of C4
OL,19,FPresentation in the 80s as being like
OL,20,Fthe BBC's but with a sense of humour
OL,21,Fand occasional mischief.
OL,23,EPub: 10-Mar-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
